2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The use of network calculus in the paper suggests a focus on networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper may also fall under this sub-category as it discusses the use of a mathematical tool (network calculus) for analyzing and controlling parallel processing systems. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - MapReduce is a well-known algorithm for processing large datasets, and the paper may touch upon the data structures and algorithms used in parallel processing systems. 
5. cs.PF (Performance) - The paper may also discuss the performance of parallel processing systems and how network calculus can be used to optimize it.
